---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Core Concepts for Muggles - Learn the Essentials"
  description="Essential coding concepts for beginners to start automating"
  lang="en"
>
  <div class="core-concepts">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-header">
        <h1>üìö Core Concepts for Muggles</h1>
        <p>Essential knowledge to get started with AI coding</p>
      </div>

      <div class="concepts-intro">
        <p>
          Before diving into complex automation, it's helpful to understand some fundamental concepts.
          Don't worry - we'll keep it simple and practical!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="concepts-grid">
        <div class="concept-card">
          <div class="concept-icon">üå≥</div>
          <h3>Git & Version Control</h3>
          <p>
            Learn how to save and track changes to your code, collaborate with others,
            and never lose your work again.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>What is Git and why it matters</li>
            <li>Basic Git commands you'll actually use</li>
            <li>GitHub for storing and sharing code</li>
            <li>How to use AI to help with Git</li>
          </ul>
          <span class="coming-soon">Coming Soon</span>
        </div>

        <div class="concept-card">
          <div class="concept-icon">üîå</div>
          <h3>API Basics</h3>
          <p>
            Understand how different applications talk to each other and how you
            can use APIs to connect your automations.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>What is an API in simple terms</li>
            <li>Reading API documentation</li>
            <li>Making your first API call</li>
            <li>Common API patterns</li>
          </ul>
          <span class="coming-soon">Coming Soon</span>
        </div>

        <div class="concept-card">
          <div class="concept-icon">üîê</div>
          <h3>Authorization & Security</h3>
          <p>
            Keep your automations secure while giving them the access they need
            to do their job.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Understanding API keys and tokens</li>
            <li>OAuth for Google Apps Script</li>
            <li>Keeping secrets secure</li>
            <li>Best practices for beginners</li>
          </ul>
          <span class="coming-soon">Coming Soon</span>
        </div>

        <div class="concept-card">
          <div class="concept-icon">ü§ñ</div>
          <h3>Using AI as Your Coding Assistant</h3>
          <p>
            Learn how to effectively communicate with AI to write, debug,
            and improve your code.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Writing good prompts for coding</li>
            <li>Understanding AI-generated code</li>
            <li>Debugging with AI help</li>
            <li>When to trust (and not trust) AI</li>
          </ul>
          <span class="coming-soon">Coming Soon</span>
        </div>

        <div class="concept-card">
          <div class="concept-icon">üìù</div>
          <h3>Working with Data</h3>
          <p>
            Learn to read, process, and transform data - the heart of most
            automation tasks.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>JSON and data formats</li>
            <li>Reading and writing files</li>
            <li>Processing spreadsheet data</li>
            <li>Basic data transformations</li>
          </ul>
          <span class="coming-soon">Coming Soon</span>
        </div>

        <div class="concept-card">
          <div class="concept-icon">‚ö°</div>
          <h3>Error Handling & Debugging</h3>
          <p>
            Don't panic when things go wrong! Learn how to find and fix errors
            in your automations.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Reading error messages</li>
            <li>Using console logs</li>
            <li>Common mistakes and how to fix them</li>
            <li>Testing your automations</li>
          </ul>
          <span class="coming-soon">Coming Soon</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cta-section">
        <h2>Ready to Start?</h2>
        <p>Don't wait until you understand everything - learning by doing is the best approach!</p>
        <a href="/blog" class="btn btn-primary">Start with a Tutorial</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .core-concepts {
    padding: 3rem 0;
  }

  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .page-header p {
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  .concepts-intro {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto 4rem;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
  }

  .concepts-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(350px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .concept-card {
    background: var(--color-bg);
    border: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .concept-icon {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .concept-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .concept-card p {
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .concept-card ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .concept-card li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .concept-card li::before {
    content: '‚úì ';
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-weight: bold;
    margin-right: 0.5rem;
  }

  .coming-soon {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--color-bg-gray);
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .cta-section {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-gray);
    border-radius: 1rem;
  }

  .cta-section h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .cta-section p {
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .concepts-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .page-header h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>

